FBIS3-30492 "dreeu024_i_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Demand Control Over Tuzla Airport Traffic AU0302145994 Paris AFP in English 1445 GMT 3 Feb 94 AU0302145994 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Belgrade, Feb 3 (AFP) -- Serb forces would agree to the reopening of the airport at Tuzla in northeast Bosnia provided they can control all the traffic going through, a Yugoslav military official was quoted as saying Thursday [3 February]. Armed Forces spokesman Colonel Ljubodrag Stojadinovic was quoted by the Bosnian Serb news agency SRNA. The United Nations is considering authorising air strikes against besieging Serb forces to obtain the reopening of Tuzla, which is considered an essential channel for humanitarian aid.
